<caption>Air break.</caption></figure>
</para><para id="id16636065">(Source: U.S. Food and Drug Administration)</para>
      </section>
      <section id="id16636070">
        <title>Air Gap</title>
        <definition id="id16636077">
          <term>Air Gap</term>
          <meaning id="oo-id16648413">The unobstructed vertical distance through the free atmosphere between the lowest opening from any pipe or outlet supplying fixture, or other device, and the flood level rim of the receptacle.
      </meaning>
        </definition>
        <para id="id16636088">The vertical physical separation must be at least two times the inside diameter of the water inlet pipe above the flood rim level, but cannot be less than one inch.</para>
        <para id="eip-773"><figure id="figure-03"><media id="airgaponlav" alt="air gap on lavatory">
