<caption>Backflow prevention devices.
</caption></figure> </para><para id="id16636197">(Source: U.S. Food and Drug Administration)</para>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section id="id16636204">
      <title>Monitoring and Management</title>
      <para id="id16636211">The management of water quality in your company is extremely important. You must develop a routine monitoring system to ensure water safety for the various uses in food production. You must also be aware of any risks posed by the design of the water conveyance system; for example, the cross- connections in the plumbing system.</para>
      <para id="id16627007">When your company commissions any new equipment that uses water, it must be monitored prior to full use to ensure that the safety of water is not compromised.</para>
    </section>
